### Test S3 Configuration Save
### This file demonstrates how the frontend saves S3 credentials to the backend

### 1. First, authenticate to get a token
POST {{backend_url}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Save configuration with S3 credentials
PUT {{backend_url}}/api/config
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "archiveWebUI": "https://archive.example.com",
  "apiToken": "PWSAK2testToken123=",
  "customerGUID": "test-guid-123",
  "s3Settings": {
    "accessKeyId": "AKIATEST123456789",
    "secretAccessKey": "testSecretKey123456789"
  }
}

### 3. Retrieve the saved configuration to verify
GET {{backend_url}}/api/config
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### Variables (set these in your REST client)
# backend_url: http://localhost:5000
# auth_token: (will be set from login response)
